-- SPAIN DAYBOOK: Iberdrola, Abertis Earnings, PM Rajoy in Rome
-- B y   A n g e l i n e   B e n o i t
-- 2012-02-23T06:44:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/spain-daybook-iberdrola-abertis-earnings-pm-rajoy-in-rome.html
The European Commission releases its
2012 growth forecast for  Spain  while Prime Minister  Mariano
Rajoy  will meet his Italian counterpart  Mario Monti  in  Rome .  WHAT TO WATCH:
-- Rajoy and Monti meet at 12 p.m. in Rome.
-- Banco Sabadell SA holds shareholders meeting to approve
capital increase.  ECONOMY:
-- The European Commission releases its 2012 growth forecast for
EU members including Spain.
-- December home mortgages are released by the National
Statistics Institute at 9 a.m. in Madrid.  EQUITY PREVIEW:
-- Mediaset Espana Comunicacion (TL5 SM) yesterday said its 2011
net profit rose to 110.5 million euros from 70.6 million euros a
year earlier.
-- Iberdrola SA (IBE SM) to publish its 2011 earnings. Analysts
expect net income of 2.84 billion euros, according to the median
of 22 estimates in a Bloomberg News survey.
-- Gamesa Corp Tecnologica SA (GAM SM) to publish its 2011
earnings. Analysts expect net income of 63.4 million euros,
according to the median of 17 estimates in a Bloomberg News
survey.
-- Indra Sistemas SA (IDR SM) to publish its 2011 earnings.
Analysts expect net income of 189 million euros, according to
the median of 23 estimates in a Bloomberg News survey.
-- Abertis Infraestructuras SA (ABE SM) said today 2011 profit
rose 8.8% to 720 million euros.  MARKETS:
-- Ibex-35 down 1.3%
-- Spanish-German 10-year yield spread 320 basis points  To contact the reporter on this story:
